- ===Noun===  + A very small, red mite endemic to the Midwestern and Southeastern US, the bite of which causes intense itching.  
- {{en-noun-reg}}  + (Verification for this usage is being sought)+: In US slang, the word Chigger (also pronounced “chigga”) is a derogatory slang term for an Asian person who behaves in ways similar to a stereotypical urban African American. The term is a portmanteau of Chinese or chink and nigger, derived from the term “wigger” (White + nigger), which refer to White Westerners who act-out urban African American stereotypes.  
-  + (Verification for this usage is being sought)+: In AUS slang, a derogatory term for a person living in the suburb of Chigwell near Hobart, Tasmania; one who resembles an inhabitant of Chigwell; a person of low socioeconomic background. Closely linked to the term westie, describes the inhabitants of notorious public housing suburbs, including but not limited to: Chigwall, Bridgewater, Gagebrook, Claredon Vale, Rokeby. Implies puffy features, mullet, underage smoking, drinking and sex, teenage pregnancy, nasty attire, poor education, sullen/antisocial behaviour and language. The suburb of Chigwell, despite its pariah status, is within 15 kilometres of the city centre. In recent years the term has been largely replaced with the more universally recognised bogan.